<br>
I am wondering how changes will be made in the game now. The &quot;boards&quot; are incredibly boring now, because it's lost it's chat room feel. It was the chat room feel that kept me coming back to the boards, and it's why I bothered commenting on the latest EQ happenings. I'm sure there are many people just like me.<br>
<br>
True, the boards could have been a LOT more civil, but I thought they got the job done reasonably well. Who knows how many improvements to the game Whineplay has brought? Gems? Spellbook gone at 35? Bug fixes? Even nerfs can be considered improvements for the game as a whole, for some nerfs really are needed. It was the constant &quot;whining&quot; of the players that got VI to change things. It was the 5 part long threads with over 1000 replies that let VI know what the players really wanted.<br>
<br>
So..what's the new Whineplay? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscacthahundredsouls.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scactha Hundredsouls</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/01 12:46:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/drexl10?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whineplay is no more</span><hr size=1> Velious expansion sucks? Yea right... <p>What´s the point of being a Hermit? Women don´t walk by mountaintops.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/30/01 1:43:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whineplay is no more</span><hr size=1> Insteading of solving the problems verant heard on the radio, they decided to turn the radio off. Thats called &quot;avoiding the issue&quot;, a real popular tactic on whineplay by Abashi and now Absor.<br>
<br>
Ill admit that there were an awful lot of worthless whining and carrying on being displayed on those boards. By the same token, there were many good ideas/concerns/issues brought forth that eventually caused the game to be changed, for better or worse. If there was no whineplay, a few of the things that PROBABLY wouldnt have ever been fixed include spell drops in kunark, alchemy, various video/framerate issues, and of corse epic encounter lag.<br>
<br>
Players now have no where to really voice their opinion. Unless you consider getting your post hacked to pieces, altered, or simply not posted voicing an opinion.<br>
<br>
Verant CS does suck. In 2 years, I have had BOTH of my accounts cease functioning for no apparent reason. Ive had CS agents ive contacted on the phone miss-enter information in their database regarding my billing, and then argue with me about it on the phone. Ive had them refuse to give me my own password after suppling ALL the information used to sign up with ( including the original cd keys ). One of the times my account ceased working, it had been hacked, and only through the help of a VERY cool gm ( who got fired weeks later for doing things like that, heh ) did we track down the guy who did it.<br>
<br>
Verants #1 problem is reading comprehension. <br>
